description.narrative: Oxfam Novib (ON) aims to be a partner and catalyst for capacity development of civil society organizations (CSOs). It is Oxfam Novibs ambition to perform this role as part of the Strategic Partnership. Within this project we aim to contribute to 2 majoroutcomes: strengthened CSOs and stronger and wider alliances. By: - Developing a framework and methodology to jointly assess and identify opportunities for CSOs and alliances on capacity development, to monitor initiatives on strengthening CSOs and alliances and to evaluateimpact achieved, especially on influencing but also on further organisational/thematic capacity needs. - Contributing on deliveringsupport for enhancing influencing, digital influencing, monitoring <(>&<)> evaluation, financial capacities and further program quality of CSOs and alliances.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
